data.title: The Rooney's Experience
data.text: This is a very laid back restaurant. You can eat inside or outside. The staff is very friendly. You are made to,feel,like you are one of the family. The burgers are fantastic. And the beer is always cold.

data.title: Lousy lunch, dirty place
data.text: The place appears dirty, grimy, and dingy.   The menus are soiled with foodstuff.   The seats need upgrading.   Very little parking available.   The food left much to be desired.   Ordered the lunch special - it was horrible.   Fish -  with spice just dumped on top of it - not prepared in the flavors as advertised (lemon pepper).   Couldn't eat it - spice too strong & lumpy.   The waitress, with no lower teeth, was pre-occupied.   Made error on check - TWICE.  Just an awful experience.

data.title: Good times had by all
data.text: Met some really fun, interesting people at Rooney's and everyone was so friendly.  Had a delicious quesadilla that was fully stuffed.  A friend enjoyed the fried shrimp dinner.   The clam chowder was fresh, loaded with clams and had a wonderful flavor.  The servers were friendly, and everyone there seemed to have a good time. Will definitely be going back.

data.title: Wonderful
data.text: Rooney's is a fun, easy going, comfortable place for lunch, dinner or just a few drinks. Lots I f smiling faces and good regular peopke. Karaoke is fun and entertaining.

data.title: Date night
data.text: My husband and I have been coming here for years and we enjoy the food and the fact that you can eat indoor or outdoor.  The staff is very friendly , and not a long wait time for food.

data.title: Rooneys Restaurant
data.text:
Been there for years, we and other people have been going for 12 of those years and the service, quality of food for the price have been above excellent.  We have ordered things from a deluxe cheeseburger w/fries(special purchase fries included) to steak and fish dinners.  All were absolutely delicious. Also we have had birthday parties and anniversary parties that had the same excellent quality dinners and service. It didn't matter if the restaurant was crowded or not. Always quality and quantity for the price.
And the help is always on your side to satisfy you.

Jeff and Maria  Palm Bay, Fl.

data.title: Love Rooneys
data.text: Very good selection of home cooking items for a most reasonable price and the service is quick and most friendly.

data.title: cool food and i do not mean  good
data.text:
heard good things about this restaurant but it did not live up to the reviews.
First appetizers (stuffed mushrooms) came out cold in middle and cheese on top was still cold.
 The main dishes were ok not really hot just warm.
 The main course was blackened Mai Mai i with backed potatoes and the potato would not even melt the butter 
The place was not real busy and it was about 6:30 Saturday night.

data.title: Kids?? What are kids?
data.text: Not kid friendly.  Asked for a kid cup and they thought we were crazy.  I thought my fish basket was gross. My husband had a shrimp po boy and thought it was okay. Not a place I would go back to.

data.title: below average food
data.text: The food is below average and comes with bad, bad service. You could pass out before anyone comes to ask if you would like a drink or food.

data.title: This WAS my go to place for fish and chips !
data.text: I have been to Rooney's several times in the past for fish and chips (featured on Friday). It has been a while so we decided to go. BIG MISTAKE...!  First warning.... they were NOT slammed (not even busy for Friday Evening)(Maybe people knew more than we did !) . So we got settled and ordered. The food came out very quickly (???? !!)  My wife likes food served HOT ; this was only warm ... (Possibly just sitting around waiting for someone to come in?? ) The overall impression of this was "never again" ! Fish and chips is NOT a complicated entree. We were very disappointed. (For $12 per person for the entree not worth it. ) We didn't try any deserts, but none are made there..... The service was good.

data.title: Good pub atmosphere
data.text: Good food at a reasonable price in a pub setting. Its a few miles from my home and is a good place to meet and dine and drink with friends.

data.title: Stopped in for a quit lunch and was pleasely surprised.
data.text: We decided to try Rooney's and were in between lunch  and dinner time we were welcomed and the atmosphere was great, food was great and the people were wonderful.

data.title: Birthday Lunch with Friends
data.text: A friend of mine took me here for lunch on my birthday.  The food was good and the service was excellent.  Highly recommend Rooney's for a good meal in a pleasant atmosphere.

data.title: Not impressed at all
data.text: The service is very slow.  The food is not very good.  The best thing they have is a butger but the burgers acriss thr street at Izzys is way better

data.title: Great Place
data.text:
We visit Rooney's a lot, great atmosphere, great food and great people. 
Friday night Fish special is the best..

data.title: Nice vintage Florida spot
data.text:
Went to Rooney's for lunch. 
there is a very nice patio off to the side where we sat. The service was wonderful, and the food was quite good. The seats though, were very uncomfortable. I asked the waitress if she had cushions, but no.

The french fries and onion rings are to die for..delicious

data.title: Enjoyed the seafood trio meal
data.text: A friend and I enjoyed an average dinner at Rooney's.  First time visit for me although I've long heard about this Palm Bay institution.  The atmosphere is casual with a full bar area.   Seat yourself.   Not too much noise emitting from the bar area (not a rowdy "young" crowd.  The patrons appeared to be of the "mature" age group.).  Our waitress appeared hurried and unfamiliar with the daily specials, soup du jour, vegetable of the day.  The seafood trio was nice - three different fish - Mahi, cod, haddock.   The fish was very tasty - prepared broiled with Cajun seasoning.   The portions were generous.   For sides, I had white corn - nothing extraordinary there - a rather small portion, and, a garden salad - again, nothing special and a bit on the skimpy side.  A bread basket with dinner rolls came with the meals.  My friend had the liver and onions with mashed potatoes and gravy along with a dinner salad.   She was not impressed with the liver - something she very much enjoys.   She left most behind.  The restrooms were clean.  The waitress could have been more attentive and refilled our beverage glasses.  The menu had a variety of items available - many comfort foods.   Fair pricing.  Ample parking.

data.title: Great family atmosphere with fun loving staff!
data.text: Went in with 5 other guests and we were seated promptly and received great customer service. The server may us feel very welcome and the food was very tasty and great value for the price.

data.title: Good times
data.text: I have been here in pairs and with groups of 15 to 20 and the service and food are always great. Prices are reasonable. Shrimp points about the best in the area.
